Subject: RE: Netwrix Support Ticket #425073 -  - 00425073 - sharepoint online not giving any result  and exchange reports are limited and not useful    [ ref:!00D70091pB.!500Qk0HTFyE:ref ]

TextBody:
Hi Kannan, we've checked logs with development team, development team's verdict is still the same, there's an issue with SSL handshake.

You've asked about PublisherIdentifier, you can refer this article as there's a description for it:

https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/office/office-365-management-api/office-365-management-activity-api-reference

We can confirm that there's nothing wrong with the PublisherIdentifier value the product uses.

Speaking of the rate limiting or throttling. If the PublisherIdentifier was not present in our requests or it was invalid/blocked, then Microsoft would impose a lower rate limit on our product. Even if that happened, the product would be able to respect the reduced limit and query data at lower rate.

If the your network team cannot find the cause, we can try to replicate the issue in a PowerShell script.

Best Regards,
Damir Akhmatshin
Support Engineer EMEA

Hi Kannan, we've checked logs with development team, development team's verdict is still the same, there's an issue with SSL handshake.

You've asked about PublisherIdentifier, you can refer this article as there's a description for it:

https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/office/office-365-management-api/office-365-management-activity-api-reference

We can confirm that there's nothing wrong with the PublisherIdentifier value the product uses.

Speaking of the rate limiting or throttling. If the PublisherIdentifier was not present in our requests or it was invalid/blocked, then Microsoft would impose a lower rate limit on our product. Even if that happened, the product would be able to respect the reduced limit and query data at lower rate.

If the your network team cannot find the cause, we can try to replicate the issue in a PowerShell script.

From: Netwrix Support <techsupport@netwrix.com>
Sent: 09 April 2025 07:02
To: Kannan Soman <kannan.soman@nhscfa.gov.uk>
Subject: RE: Netwrix Support Ticket #425073 - - 00425073 - sharepoint online not giving any result and exchange reports are limited and not useful [ ref:!00D70091pB.!500Qk0HTFyE:ref ]



 


	
		
			 
			
			
			Caution: This email originated from outside of NHS Counter Fraud Authority. DO NOT click links or open attachments unless you are sure the content is safe. 
			
			
		
	


 


Hi Kannan, we've checked logs with development team, development team's verdict is still the same, there's an issue with SSL handshake.

You've asked about PublisherIdentifier, you can refer this article as there's a description for it:

https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/office/office-365-management-api/office-365-management-activity-api-reference

We can confirm that there's nothing wrong with the PublisherIdentifier value the product uses.

Speaking of the rate limiting or throttling. If the PublisherIdentifier was not present in our requests or it was invalid/blocked, then Microsoft would impose a lower rate limit on our product. Even if that happened, the product would be able to respect the reduced limit and query data at lower rate.

If the your network team cannot find the cause, we can try to replicate the issue in a PowerShell script.

TextBody:
Hi Kannan, we would need to run a Powershell script on upcoming meeting, you can find this script below:

Add-Type -AssemblyName System.Web
Add-Type -AssemblyName System.Net.Http
$installPath = Get-ItemPropertyValue -Path "HKLM:SOFTWARENetwrix Activity Monitor Agent 64-bit" -Name InstallLocation
$agentVersion = Get-ItemPropertyValue -Path "HKLM:SOFTWARENetwrix Activity Monitor Agent 64-bit" -Name Version
cd "$installPathnet472"
$httpHandler = [System.Net.Http.HttpClientHandler]::new()
$client = [System.Net.Http.HttpClient]::new($httpHandler)
$client.Timeout = [System.TimeSpan]::FromSeconds(180)
$client.DefaultRequestHeaders.Add("User-Agent", "ISV|Netwrix|Activity Monitor|$agentVersion")
$request = [System.Net.Http.HttpRequestMessage]::new([System.Net.Http.HttpMethod]::Get, "https://manage.office.com/api/v1.0/071ca16e-d213-461f-9ab1-081b0144c15a/activity/feed/subscriptions/list?PublisherIdentifier=097499ff-179d-4959-ab02-86d364125bfc")
$request.Headers.Authorization = [System.Net.Http.Headers.AuthenticationHeaderValue]::new("Bearer", "abc")
$request.Headers.Accept.Add([System.Net.Http.Headers.MediaTypeWithQualityHeaderValue]::new("application/json"))
$client.SendAsync($request).Result

Hi Kannan, we've checked logs with development team, development team's verdict is still the same, there's an issue with SSL handshake.

You've asked about PublisherIdentifier, you can refer this article as there's a description for it:

https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/office/office-365-management-api/office-365-management-activity-api-reference

We can confirm that there's nothing wrong with the PublisherIdentifier value the product uses.

Speaking of the rate limiting or throttling. If the PublisherIdentifier was not present in our requests or it was invalid/blocked, then Microsoft would impose a lower rate limit on our product. Even if that happened, the product would be able to respect the reduced limit and query data at lower rate.

If the your network team cannot find the cause, we can try to replicate the issue in a PowerShell script.

Best Regards,

Subject: RE: Netwrix Support Ticket #425073 -  - 00425073 - sharepoint online not giving any result  and exchange reports are limited and not useful    [ ref:!00D70091pB.!500Qk0HTFyE:ref ]

TextBody:
Hi Kannan, thank you for your time on meeting today, we've reviewed the current status of the issue. We've ran the Powershell script and confirmed the same behaviour even outside of our application, there must me a network issue with SSL when connecting to manage.office.com.

Suggestions from our team are following:

1. Check firewall output and if there's any blocking for manage.office.com.
2. Install Netwrix Activity Monitor agent to a different host and confirm or deny on observing the same behaviour.

Regarding SPAA jobs - they do not use Activity Monitor agent, so upgrade of the Netwrix Activity Monitor shouldn't have to affect those jobs, instead in logs you've provided I can see this entry that suggests that FIPS is enabled and might be interfering workflow of our jobs, so this issue might have occurred after Netwrix Access Analyzer was upgraded.

08/04/2025 05:41:25  DEBUG  SHAREPOINTACCESS  Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.SPAA.Tasks.ScanSharePointAccessTask.InternalProcessRecord  "[C:70] Failure processing Resource(SiteCollection|733|RH-Test Team - Test Private Channel 2).ISharePointGroup Child:null Error Details: Message=Exception has been thrown by the target of an invocation.  Source=mscorlib  Type=System.Reflection.TargetInvocationException  Data=EMPTY  StackTrace=   at System.RuntimeMethodHandle.InvokeMethod(Object target, Object[] arguments, Signature sig, Boolean constructor)     at System.Reflection.RuntimeConstructorInfo.Invoke(BindingFlags invokeAttr, Binder binder, Object[] parameters, CultureInfo culture)     at System.Security.Cryptography.CryptoConfig.CreateFromName(String name, Object[] args)     at System.Security.Cryptography.MD5.Create()     at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.SPAA.AccountManagement.TrusteeHelper.GetLoginNameHashAlgorithm()     at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.SPAA.AccountManagement.TrusteeHelper.CreateSecurityIdentifierFromSiteCollectionLoginName(Int64 siteCollectionId, String loginName)     at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.SPAA.Scanning.SharePointTasks.GetOrCreateTrusteeFromGroup(ISharePointGroup group, Resource resource)     at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.SPAA.Scanning.SharePointTasks.ProcessSiteCollection_StoreGroup(ISharePointGroup group, Resource siteCollectionResource, Object& state)     at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.SPAA.Scanning.SharePointTasks.<>c__DisplayClass20_0`2.<ProcessQuery_Enumerate>b__1(TResult o, Resource r)     at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.SPAA.Scanning.SharePointTasks.QueryEnumerate[TSource,TResult](Func`3 query, TSource parentSharePointObject, Resource parentResource, Action`2 processChild, String processingDescription)  HResult=-2146232828  InnerException=    Message=This implementation is not part of the Windows Platform FIPS validated cryptographic algorithms.    Source=mscorlib    Type=System.InvalidOperationException    Data=EMPTY    StackTrace=   at System.Security.Cryptography.MD5CryptoServiceProvider..ctor()    HResult=-2146233079  " 

This is a different issue that is not related with Activity Monitor.

I can recommend trying if temporary disabling FIPS works as first troubleshooting step:
 

	On the computer where Netwrix Access Analyzer is installed, open Registry Editor.
	
	Go to the following path: HKLMSystemCurrentControlSetControlLsaFIPSAlgorithmPolicyEnabled. This registry value reflects the current FIPS setting.
	
	Set the value to 0 for disabled.
	

Please log a separate ticket to cover this issue.

Hi Kannan, we've checked logs with development team, development team's verdict is still the same, there's an issue with SSL handshake.

You've asked about PublisherIdentifier, you can refer this article as there's a description for it:

https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/office/office-365-management-api/office-365-management-activity-api-reference

We can confirm that there's nothing wrong with the PublisherIdentifier value the product uses.

Speaking of the rate limiting or throttling. If the PublisherIdentifier was not present in our requests or it was invalid/blocked, then Microsoft would impose a lower rate limit on our product. Even if that happened, the product would be able to respect the reduced limit and query data at lower rate.

If the your network team cannot find the cause, we can try to replicate the issue in a PowerShell script.

From: Netwrix Support [techsupport@netwrix.com]
Sent: 4/10/2025 3:41 PM
To: kannan.soman@nhscfa.gov.uk
Subject: RE: Netwrix Support Ticket #425073 - - 00425073 - sharepoint online not giving any result and exchange reports are limited and not useful [ ref:!00D70091pB.!500Qk0HTFyE:ref ]

Hi Kannan, thank you for your time on meeting today, we've reviewed the current status of the issue. We've ran the Powershell script and confirmed the same behaviour even outside of our application, there must me a network issue with SSL when connecting to manage.office.com.

Suggestions from our team are following:

1. Check firewall output and if there's any blocking for manage.office.com.
2. Install Netwrix Activity Monitor agent to a different host and confirm or deny on observing the same behaviour.

Regarding SPAA jobs - they do not use Activity Monitor agent, so upgrade of the Netwrix Activity Monitor shouldn't have to affect those jobs, instead in logs you've provided I can see this entry that suggests that FIPS is enabled and might be interfering workflow of our jobs, so this issue might have occurred after Netwrix Access Analyzer was upgraded.

08/04/2025 05:41:25  DEBUG  SHAREPOINTACCESS  Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.SPAA.Tasks.ScanSharePointAccessTask.InternalProcessRecord  "[C:70] Failure processing Resource(SiteCollection|733|RH-Test Team - Test Private Channel 2).ISharePointGroup Child:null Error Details: Message=Exception has been thrown by the target of an invocation.  Source=mscorlib  Type=System.Reflection.TargetInvocationException  Data=EMPTY  StackTrace=   at System.RuntimeMethodHandle.InvokeMethod(Object target, Object[] arguments, Signature sig, Boolean constructor)     at System.Reflection.RuntimeConstructorInfo.Invoke(BindingFlags invokeAttr, Binder binder, Object[] parameters, CultureInfo culture)     at System.Security.Cryptography.CryptoConfig.CreateFromName(String name, Object[] args)     at System.Security.Cryptography.MD5.Create()     at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.SPAA.AccountManagement.TrusteeHelper.GetLoginNameHashAlgorithm()     at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.SPAA.AccountManagement.TrusteeHelper.CreateSecurityIdentifierFromSiteCollectionLoginName(Int64 siteCollectionId, String loginName)     at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.SPAA.Scanning.SharePointTasks.GetOrCreateTrusteeFromGroup(ISharePointGroup group, Resource resource)     at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.SPAA.Scanning.SharePointTasks.ProcessSiteCollection_StoreGroup(ISharePointGroup group, Resource siteCollectionResource, Object& state)     at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.SPAA.Scanning.SharePointTasks.<>c__DisplayClass20_0`2.<ProcessQuery_Enumerate>b__1(TResult o, Resource r)     at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.SPAA.Scanning.SharePointTasks.QueryEnumerate[TSource,TResult](Func`3 query, TSource parentSharePointObject, Resource parentResource, Action`2 processChild, String processingDescription)  HResult=-2146232828  InnerException=    Message=This implementation is not part of the Windows Platform FIPS validated cryptographic algorithms.    Source=mscorlib    Type=System.InvalidOperationException    Data=EMPTY    StackTrace=   at System.Security.Cryptography.MD5CryptoServiceProvider..ctor()    HResult=-2146233079  " 

This is a different issue that is not related with Activity Monitor.

I can recommend trying if temporary disabling FIPS works as first troubleshooting step:
 

	On the computer where Netwrix Access Analyzer is installed, open Registry Editor.
	
	Go to the following path: HKLMSystemCurrentControlSetControlLsaFIPSAlgorithmPolicyEnabled. This registry value reflects the current FIPS setting.
	
	Set the value to 0 for disabled.
	

Please log a separate ticket to cover this issue.

Best Regards,
Damir Akhmatshin
Support Engineer EMEA

Hi Kannan, we've checked logs with development team, development team's verdict is still the same, there's an issue with SSL handshake.

You've asked about PublisherIdentifier, you can refer this article as there's a description for it:

https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/office/office-365-management-api/office-365-management-activity-api-reference

We can confirm that there's nothing wrong with the PublisherIdentifier value the product uses.

Speaking of the rate limiting or throttling. If the PublisherIdentifier was not present in our requests or it was invalid/blocked, then Microsoft would impose a lower rate limit on our product. Even if that happened, the product would be able to respect the reduced limit and query data at lower rate.

If the your network team cannot find the cause, we can try to replicate the issue in a PowerShell script.

Best Regards,

Hi Kannan, thank you for your time on meeting today, we've reviewed the current status of the issue. We've ran the Powershell script and confirmed the same behaviour even outside of our application, there must me a network issue with SSL when connecting to manage.office.com.

Suggestions from our team are following:

1. Check firewall output and if there's any blocking for manage.office.com.
2. Install Netwrix Activity Monitor agent to a different host and confirm or deny on observing the same behaviour.

Regarding SPAA jobs - they do not use Activity Monitor agent, so upgrade of the Netwrix Activity Monitor shouldn't have to affect those jobs, instead in logs you've provided I can see this entry that suggests that FIPS is enabled and might be interfering workflow of our jobs, so this issue might have occurred after Netwrix Access Analyzer was upgraded.

08/04/2025 05:41:25  DEBUG  SHAREPOINTACCESS  Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.SPAA.Tasks.ScanSharePointAccessTask.InternalProcessRecord  "[C:70] Failure processing Resource(SiteCollection|733|RH-Test Team - Test Private Channel 2).ISharePointGroup Child:null Error Details: Message=Exception has been thrown by the target of an invocation.  Source=mscorlib  Type=System.Reflection.TargetInvocationException  Data=EMPTY  StackTrace=   at System.RuntimeMethodHandle.InvokeMethod(Object target, Object[] arguments, Signature sig, Boolean constructor)     at System.Reflection.RuntimeConstructorInfo.Invoke(BindingFlags invokeAttr, Binder binder, Object[] parameters, CultureInfo culture)     at System.Security.Cryptography.CryptoConfig.CreateFromName(String name, Object[] args)     at System.Security.Cryptography.MD5.Create()     at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.SPAA.AccountManagement.TrusteeHelper.GetLoginNameHashAlgorithm()     at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.SPAA.AccountManagement.TrusteeHelper.CreateSecurityIdentifierFromSiteCollectionLoginName(Int64 siteCollectionId, String loginName)     at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.SPAA.Scanning.SharePointTasks.GetOrCreateTrusteeFromGroup(ISharePointGroup group, Resource resource)     at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.SPAA.Scanning.SharePointTasks.ProcessSiteCollection_StoreGroup(ISharePointGroup group, Resource siteCollectionResource, Object& state)     at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.SPAA.Scanning.SharePointTasks.<>c__DisplayClass20_0`2.<ProcessQuery_Enumerate>b__1(TResult o, Resource r)     at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.SPAA.Scanning.SharePointTasks.QueryEnumerate[TSource,TResult](Func`3 query, TSource parentSharePointObject, Resource parentResource, Action`2 processChild, String processingDescription)  HResult=-2146232828  InnerException=    Message=This implementation is not part of the Windows Platform FIPS validated cryptographic algorithms.    Source=mscorlib    Type=System.InvalidOperationException    Data=EMPTY    StackTrace=   at System.Security.Cryptography.MD5CryptoServiceProvider..ctor()    HResult=-2146233079  " 

This is a different issue that is not related with Activity Monitor.

I can recommend trying if temporary disabling FIPS works as first troubleshooting step:


  1.  On the computer where Netwrix Access Analyzer is installed, open Registry Editor.
  2.  Go to the following path: HKLMSystemCurrentControlSetControlLsaFIPSAlgorithmPolicyEnabled. This registry value reflects the current FIPS setting.
  3.  Set the value to 0 for disabled.

Please log a separate ticket to cover this issue.

Best Regards,

Hi Kannan, we've checked logs with development team, development team's verdict is still the same, there's an issue with SSL handshake.

You've asked about PublisherIdentifier, you can refer this article as there's a description for it:

https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/office/office-365-management-api/office-365-management-activity-api-reference

We can confirm that there's nothing wrong with the PublisherIdentifier value the product uses.

Speaking of the rate limiting or throttling. If the PublisherIdentifier was not present in our requests or it was invalid/blocked, then Microsoft would impose a lower rate limit on our product. Even if that happened, the product would be able to respect the reduced limit and query data at lower rate.

If the your network team cannot find the cause, we can try to replicate the issue in a PowerShell script.

Hi Kannan, thank you for your time on meeting today, we've reviewed the current status of the issue. We've ran the Powershell script and confirmed the same behaviour even outside of our application, there must me a network issue with SSL when connecting to manage.office.com.

Suggestions from our team are following:

1. Check firewall output and if there's any blocking for manage.office.com.
2. Install Netwrix Activity Monitor agent to a different host and confirm or deny on observing the same behaviour.

Regarding SPAA jobs - they do not use Activity Monitor agent, so upgrade of the Netwrix Activity Monitor shouldn't have to affect those jobs, instead in logs you've provided I can see this entry that suggests that FIPS is enabled and might be interfering workflow of our jobs, so this issue might have occurred after Netwrix Access Analyzer was upgraded.

08/04/2025 05:41:25  DEBUG  SHAREPOINTACCESS  Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.SPAA.Tasks.ScanSharePointAccessTask.InternalProcessRecord  "[C:70] Failure processing Resource(SiteCollection|733|RH-Test Team - Test Private Channel 2).ISharePointGroup Child:null Error Details: Message=Exception has been thrown by the target of an invocation.  Source=mscorlib  Type=System.Reflection.TargetInvocationException  Data=EMPTY  StackTrace=   at System.RuntimeMethodHandle.InvokeMethod(Object target, Object[] arguments, Signature sig, Boolean constructor)     at System.Reflection.RuntimeConstructorInfo.Invoke(BindingFlags invokeAttr, Binder binder, Object[] parameters, CultureInfo culture)     at System.Security.Cryptography.CryptoConfig.CreateFromName(String name, Object[] args)     at System.Security.Cryptography.MD5.Create()     at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.SPAA.AccountManagement.TrusteeHelper.GetLoginNameHashAlgorithm()     at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.SPAA.AccountManagement.TrusteeHelper.CreateSecurityIdentifierFromSiteCollectionLoginName(Int64 siteCollectionId, String loginName)     at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.SPAA.Scanning.SharePointTasks.GetOrCreateTrusteeFromGroup(ISharePointGroup group, Resource resource)     at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.SPAA.Scanning.SharePointTasks.ProcessSiteCollection_StoreGroup(ISharePointGroup group, Resource siteCollectionResource, Object& state)     at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.SPAA.Scanning.SharePointTasks.<>c__DisplayClass20_0`2.<ProcessQuery_Enumerate>b__1(TResult o, Resource r)     at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.SPAA.Scanning.SharePointTasks.QueryEnumerate[TSource,TResult](Func`3 query, TSource parentSharePointObject, Resource parentResource, Action`2 processChild, String processingDescription)  HResult=-2146232828  InnerException=    Message=This implementation is not part of the Windows Platform FIPS validated cryptographic algorithms.    Source=mscorlib    Type=System.InvalidOperationException    Data=EMPTY    StackTrace=   at System.Security.Cryptography.MD5CryptoServiceProvider..ctor()    HResult=-2146233079  " 

This is a different issue that is not related with Activity Monitor.

I can recommend trying if temporary disabling FIPS works as first troubleshooting step:


  1.  On the computer where Netwrix Access Analyzer is installed, open Registry Editor.
  2.  Go to the following path: HKLMSystemCurrentControlSetControlLsaFIPSAlgorithmPolicyEnabled. This registry value reflects the current FIPS setting.
  3.  Set the value to 0 for disabled.

Please log a separate ticket to cover this issue.

Best Regards,

Hi Kannan, we've checked logs with development team, development team's verdict is still the same, there's an issue with SSL handshake.

You've asked about PublisherIdentifier, you can refer this article as there's a description for it:

https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/office/office-365-management-api/office-365-management-activity-api-reference

We can confirm that there's nothing wrong with the PublisherIdentifier value the product uses.

Speaking of the rate limiting or throttling. If the PublisherIdentifier was not present in our requests or it was invalid/blocked, then Microsoft would impose a lower rate limit on our product. Even if that happened, the product would be able to respect the reduced limit and query data at lower rate.

If the your network team cannot find the cause, we can try to replicate the issue in a PowerShell script.

Best Regards,

From: Netwrix Support [techsupport@netwrix.com]
Sent: 4/10/2025 3:41 PM
To: kannan.soman@nhscfa.gov.uk
Subject: RE: Netwrix Support Ticket #425073 - - 00425073 - sharepoint online not giving any result and exchange reports are limited and not useful [ ref:!00D70091pB.!500Qk0HTFyE:ref ]

Hi Kannan, thank you for your time on meeting today, we've reviewed the current status of the issue. We've ran the Powershell script and confirmed the same behaviour even outside of our application, there must me a network issue with SSL when connecting to manage.office.com.

Suggestions from our team are following:

1. Check firewall output and if there's any blocking for manage.office.com.
2. Install Netwrix Activity Monitor agent to a different host and confirm or deny on observing the same behaviour.

Regarding SPAA jobs - they do not use Activity Monitor agent, so upgrade of the Netwrix Activity Monitor shouldn't have to affect those jobs, instead in logs you've provided I can see this entry that suggests that FIPS is enabled and might be interfering workflow of our jobs, so this issue might have occurred after Netwrix Access Analyzer was upgraded.

08/04/2025 05:41:25  DEBUG  SHAREPOINTACCESS  Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.SPAA.Tasks.ScanSharePointAccessTask.InternalProcessRecord  "[C:70] Failure processing Resource(SiteCollection|733|RH-Test Team - Test Private Channel 2).ISharePointGroup Child:null Error Details: Message=Exception has been thrown by the target of an invocation.  Source=mscorlib  Type=System.Reflection.TargetInvocationException  Data=EMPTY  StackTrace=   at System.RuntimeMethodHandle.InvokeMethod(Object target, Object[] arguments, Signature sig, Boolean constructor)     at System.Reflection.RuntimeConstructorInfo.Invoke(BindingFlags invokeAttr, Binder binder, Object[] parameters, CultureInfo culture)     at System.Security.Cryptography.CryptoConfig.CreateFromName(String name, Object[] args)     at System.Security.Cryptography.MD5.Create()     at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.SPAA.AccountManagement.TrusteeHelper.GetLoginNameHashAlgorithm()     at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.SPAA.AccountManagement.TrusteeHelper.CreateSecurityIdentifierFromSiteCollectionLoginName(Int64 siteCollectionId, String loginName)     at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.SPAA.Scanning.SharePointTasks.GetOrCreateTrusteeFromGroup(ISharePointGroup group, Resource resource)     at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.SPAA.Scanning.SharePointTasks.ProcessSiteCollection_StoreGroup(ISharePointGroup group, Resource siteCollectionResource, Object& state)     at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.SPAA.Scanning.SharePointTasks.<>c__DisplayClass20_0`2.<ProcessQuery_Enumerate>b__1(TResult o, Resource r)     at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.SPAA.Scanning.SharePointTasks.QueryEnumerate[TSource,TResult](Func`3 query, TSource parentSharePointObject, Resource parentResource, Action`2 processChild, String processingDescription)  HResult=-2146232828  InnerException=    Message=This implementation is not part of the Windows Platform FIPS validated cryptographic algorithms.    Source=mscorlib    Type=System.InvalidOperationException    Data=EMPTY    StackTrace=   at System.Security.Cryptography.MD5CryptoServiceProvider..ctor()    HResult=-2146233079  " 

This is a different issue that is not related with Activity Monitor.

I can recommend trying if temporary disabling FIPS works as first troubleshooting step:
 

On the computer where Netwrix Access Analyzer is installed, open Registry Editor.Go to the following path: HKLMSystemCurrentControlSetControlLsaFIPSAlgorithmPolicyEnabled. This registry value reflects the current FIPS setting.Set the value to 0 for disabled.

Please log a separate ticket to cover this issue.

Best Regards,

Hi Kannan, we've checked logs with development team, development team's verdict is still the same, there's an issue with SSL handshake.

You've asked about PublisherIdentifier, you can refer this article as there's a description for it:

https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/office/office-365-management-api/office-365-management-activity-api-reference

We can confirm that there's nothing wrong with the PublisherIdentifier value the product uses.

Speaking of the rate limiting or throttling. If the PublisherIdentifier was not present in our requests or it was invalid/blocked, then Microsoft would impose a lower rate limit on our product. Even if that happened, the product would be able to respect the reduced limit and query data at lower rate.

If the your network team cannot find the cause, we can try to replicate the issue in a PowerShell script.

Best Regards,

Subject: RE: Netwrix Support Ticket #425073 -  - 00425073 - sharepoint online not giving any result  and exchange reports are limited and not useful    [ ref:!00D70091pB.!500Qk0HTFyE:ref ]

TextBody:
Hi Kannan, thank you for your time on meeting, today we've confirmed that activity is getting gathered by the agent and SPAC Scan and SPAC Bulk import both working correctly.

The root cause for the issue was connection issue for Netwrix Activity Monitor agent to Sharepoint server to collect activity, following that we needed to add proper configuration to SPAC collector.

As agreed on meeting, I will close this ticket.

Please feel free to leave any feedback, it will help us to be more effective and productive.

P.S

On meeting we've discovered that your accounts do not have admin access in Access Information Center, as promised on meeting here's an article on console access levels:

https://helpcenter.netwrix.com/bundle/AIC_12.0/page/Content/Access/InformationCenter/Admin/Configuration/ConsoleAccess.htm

At the very bottom of this article there's an instruction on how to reset admin account if needed.


Best Regards,
Damir Akhmatshin
Support Engineer EMEA

300 Spectrum Ctr Dr #200, Irvine, CA 92618
www.netwrix.com
